#-Function--onoff
  Function: onoff
      Desc: return 1 if 'on', 0 if 'off'
  Synopsis: onoff [on|1] | [off|0]] [defaultval]
          : for ambiguous value, return 'defaultval' if defined, otherwise return 0.
   Example: result=$(onoff off 1)
#-Function--onoff-------------------------------------------------------------
